<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink133-kilavi">
        vāyilāyp pukunta pāṇaṉ talaimakaḷ tōḷmelivu kaṇṭu maṉaippuṟattup pōyvanta tuṇaiyāṉē ivvāṟu vēṟupaṭutal takātu eṉṟāṟku avaḷ colliyatu.</p>    <p xml:lang="en">
          Spoken by her (the heroine) to him (the bard) who said, ’Such a change because of the aprtner who went out of the house [and] came [back] will not be appropriate’ [the bard] who entered through the entrance, having seen the softness of the heroine’s shoulders.
 </p>
 </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink133">
<l>yāṉevaṉ ceykō pāṇavā ṉātu</l>
<l>mellam pulampaṉ pirinteṉap</l>
<l>pulleṉ ṟaṉaveṉ purivaḷait tōḷē</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
  <l>What do I do, oh bard?</l>
    <l>My shoulders with twisted bangles have become endlessly dull,</l>
      <l>Since the man of the soft, pretty, maritime tract has separated [from me].</l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
